, 
<figureCitation id="9EFA2A2F543CFFB860FDFEADFE48FEBC" box="[465,482,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,193,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[153,1433,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 7. Stigmella apicibrunella Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 2 — habitat, western slopes of the equatorial Andes (Ecuador: Chimborazo Province) at altitudes about 1800 m; 3 — host plant Acalypha padifolia Kunth (Euphorbiaceae); 4, leafmines; 5 – 7, female paratype adults." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/583343/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">2</figureCitation>
). This species occurs on the western slopes of the equatorial Andes (
<collectingCountry id="7ED6763A543CFFB86419FEADFA32FEBD" box="[1333,1432,332,357]" name="Ecuador" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
