<subSubSection id="4EDB6521543CFFB861EBFE75FD37FE17" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="067E36AA543CFFB861EBFE75FD37FE17" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="34B5EAB8543CFFB861EBFE75FEE4FE75" bold="true" box="[199,334,404,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from Latin 
<emphasis id="34B5EAB8543CFFB86234FE74FCFFFE74" box="[792,853,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">apice</emphasis>
(apex) and 
<emphasis id="34B5EAB8543CFFB862F6FE75FB82FE74" box="[986,1064,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">brunus</emphasis>
(brown) in reference to the color of the forewing with a distinctive brown apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
